pulated with drunks, loggers, card sharks, and whores, but also one rich in the pleasures of fly-fishing, logging, cribbage, and family. By turns raunchy and elegiac, these superb tales express, in Maclean’s own words, “a little of the love I have for the earth as it goes by.”  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aBrothersvFiction. 0aFathers and sonsvFiction. 0aFly fishingvFiction. 0aOutdoor recreationvFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aa river runs thru it, Logging and Pimping and Your pal Jim, USFS 1919 The Ranger the Cook and a Hole in the Sky, American classic novels, American classic stories, coming off age novel, pulitzer prize books, pulitzer prize fiction, rural America fiction, fly fishing stories, Big Blackfoot River novel, nature novel, United States Forest Service, wilderness fiction story, 20th century rural America, fishing Montana, Montana novel, filmed novel, 20th century stories, alcoholism and gambling, logging camps.1 aRedford, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRedford, Robert.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311071193640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226472232423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226472232/original  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles